```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Integer=3)
    if !(isa(dt, DateTime))
        throw(ArgumentError("Input must be a DateTime type"))
    end
    return dt + Dates.Hour(bump)
end
```

This function will add `bump` hours to the provided `DateTime` object and return the updated timestamp. If no `bump` is specified, it defaults to adding 3 hours. The function checks that the input is a `DateTime` type and throws an error if it's not.
